        "now have budget splits of 60/40 in favour of avionics.      The civilian market has also seen a growth in cost of avionics. Flight control systems  and new navigation needs brought on by tighter airspaces, have pushed up development costs. The major change has been the recent boom in consumer flying. As more people begin to use planes as their primary method of transportation, more elaborate methods of controlling aircraft safely in these high restrictive airspaces have been invented.       Avionics plays a heavy role in modernization initiatives like the ": null
