        ".     International standards for avionics equipment are prepared by the Airlines Electronic Engineering Committee and published by ARINC.         Communications connect the flight deck to the ground and the flight deck to the passengers. On‑board communications are provided by public-address systems and aircraft intercoms.     The VHF aviation communication system works on the ": null
    },
    {
        "airband": "Airband"
    },
    {
        " of 118.000  MHz to 136.975  MHz. Each channel is spaced from the adjacent ones by 8.33  kHz in Europe, 25  kHz elsewhere. VHF is also used for line of sight communication such as aircraft-to-aircraft and aircraft-to-ATC. ": null
    },
    {
        "Amplitude modulation": "Amplitude Modulation"
    },
    {
        " is used, and the conversation is performed in ": null
    },
    {
        "simplex": "Simplex Communication"
    },
    {
        " mode. Aircraft communication can also take place using HF or satellite communication.                 ": null
