    },
    {
        "radio navigation": "Radio Navigation"
    },
    {
        " systems , or any combination thereof. Some navigation systems such as GPS calculate the position automatically and display it to the flight crew on moving map displays. Older ground-based Navigation systems such as VOR or LORAN requires a pilot or navigator to plot the intersection of signals on a paper map to determine an aircrafts location; modern systems calculate the position automatically and display it to the flight crew on moving map displays.             The first hints of ": null
